<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-78-0267 </DOCNO><TEXT>New digital imaging modalities and more sophisticated image processingsystems will have a profound effect on those areas of medicine concernedwith imaging. This mainly means computer-assisted radiology (CAR) andimplies a transition from analog film systems to digital imaging systems,integration of digital imaging modalities through picture archiving andcommunication systems (PACS) and the graduated employment of image-orientedmedical work stations (MWS) for computer-assisted representation, communication,diagnosis, and therapy planning.</TEXT></DOC>